            <title>[KAFKA-1496] Using batch message in sync producer only sends the first message if we use a Scala Stream as the argument </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1496</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I am passing a Scala Stream to the producer as followed:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;producer.send(events.toSeq:*)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The events was a Scala Stream of KeyedMessages. In sync mode, it will only send one message to Kafka while in async mode it was fine. I tracked down the issue and I&apos;m attaching a fix for it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
